Add support for arbitrary currencies that are not part of ISO 4217
Suppress warning from PHPMD's ExcessiveClassLength rule
Use absolute namespaces in phpdoc to ease understanding by most IDEAs (ie: PHPStorm)
Update license and copyright in all files
Update license and copyright in all files
Update license and copyright in all files

Provide new functionality to ensure that internal operations don't disguise imprecision
In certain cases it is possible for the Money object to deal in numbers which overflow the integer limit of PHP this introduces errors that a users of the package will not be aware of. This commit causes failure by throwing an exception when a to-be-cast number is out of integer

create method to retrieve amount converted to base units
`getConvertedAmount` converts the `Money`s value into its base units (dollars, euros, etc) and rounds to the appropriate digits.
update the `IntlFormatter` to use this new method.
Update license and copyright in all files
Use absolute namespaces in phpdoc to ease understanding by most IDEAs (ie: PHPStorm)

create method to retrieve amount converted to base units
`getConvertedAmount` converts the `Money`s value into its base units (dollars, euros, etc) and rounds to the appropriate digits.
update the `IntlFormatter` to use this new method.
Update license and copyright in all files

Added RoundingMode for extractPercentage method
See rules for rounding VAT of Dutch VAT Agency: http://www.belastingdienst.nl/wps/wcm/connect/bldcontentnl/belastingdienst/zakelijk/btw/administratie_bijhouden/facturen_maken/btw-bedrag_afronden
Translation: You use for the completion of the amount of VAT the arithmetic method. If the amount of VAT due on the invoice consists of more than two decimal places, it rounds to the 3rd decimal place off to whole cents. This is done as follows:
Implement Money::extractPercentage() to extract a percentage and the corresponding subtotal; see #27
Allow ISO 4217 currency code as second constructor argument

Throw more informative exceptions when addition and subtract cause overflow
Currently an InvalidArgumentException is thrown during overflow causing addition and subtract.
This exception type is not very informative, and because it is an internal operation that is causing it, a more informative exception

Provide new functionality to ensure that internal operations don't disguise imprecision
In certain cases it is possible for the Money object to deal in numbers which overflow the integer limit of PHP this introduces errors that a users of the package will not be aware of. This commit causes failure by throwing an exception when a to-be-cast number is out of integer
Added late static binding to newMoney() method
Added Money::equals(), Money::greaterThanOrEqual() and Money::lessThanOrEqual() methods
Use absolute namespaces in phpdoc to ease understanding by most IDEAs (ie: PHPStorm)
